						               													<description>Crime Writers is a unique crime game that - besides providing the exciting atmosphere of solving a murder - also challenges the writing skills of the players.&amp;#10;The original black and white photos evoke the mood of classical crime fiction as well as the visuality of suspense and film noir movies. &amp;#10;The crime element cards are really inspirational without exercising too much influence on the storytelling process.&amp;#10;It is a card-based cooperative creative party game with semi-competitive elements.&amp;#10;It contains 86 cards that represent the five basic elements of a crime story in four stacks of cards: crime scene, killer/victim, motive, cause of death. &amp;#10;The game has two stages. The first is the writing stage, where everyone writes a story of a crime using the elements from the cards they have drawn.&amp;#10;In the second stage, the player who's turn it is becomes the writer and the others become guests.&amp;#10;The guests try to reveal the crime story by asking and guessing and try to figure out the whole story, observing the rules of asking.&amp;#10;The guests must continue until they can make all the connections and tell the whole story.&amp;#10;The game only comes to an end once the story of every player has been found out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An exciting card game for any party of teenagers and adults.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing Time: 15-20 min./player&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
